<br>
Racial traits are good diversion in a rpg style game, they grant a sense of uniqueness and usually allow for customization of one's play style. Given the nature of the everquest engine and it's limits there really can't be any differences overall, varried play styles are not encouraged nor are they handled. When you have only a handfull of all the avaliable races having some kind of unique perk that is often times meaningless then it makes no design sense, it's about time the team in charge realized this. <br>
<br>
Ogres paid for their 100% frontal stun immunity on the route to 60, they do not pay again for those advantages while working aa's. The will once again pay for it making the trek from 60 to 65, while not having to lose time <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> aa xp'n</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to gain an ability that is a lesser clone of what you get innately. Make sense? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mofufoulsoul>Mofu Foulsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 4:10:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2202.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A bonus?</span><hr size=1> heh he said full frontal<br>
